---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About & CV"
	description="Microbiome Informatics Researcher & Bioinformatics Engineer"
	pubDate={new Date('2026-03-13')}
  category="Researcher Profile"
>
	<div class="about-container">
		<p class="intro">
			Hi, I'm <strong>alienzj</strong>. I am a researcher and bioinformatics engineer 
      dedicated to building tools for microbiome informatics and AI-powered scientific workflows.
		</p>

		<section>
			<h2>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="section-icon"><path d="M10 2v7.31"/><path d="M14 9.3V1.99"/><path d="M8.5 2h7"/><path d="M14 9.3a6.5 6.5 0 1 1-4 0"/><path d="M5.52 16h12.96"/></svg>
        Research & Work
      </h2>
			<p>
				My work centers on <strong>metagenomics</strong> and the development of 
        robust, reproducible pipelines. I focus on Metagenome-Assembled Genomes (MAGs) 
        and high-throughput data analysis.
			</p>
      <p>
        I am a co-founder of <strong>OhMeta</strong>, where I develop tools like 
        <code>metapi</code>, <code>quantpi</code>, <code>rnapi</code>, <code>qiimepi</code>, 
        <code>skillpi</code>, and <code>clawpi</code>.
      </p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="section-icon"><rect x="9" y="9" width="6" height="6"/><path d="M15 2v2"/><path d="M15 20v2"/><path d="M2 15h2"/><path d="M2 9h2"/><path d="M20 15h2"/><path d="M20 9h2"/><path d="M9 2v2"/><path d="M9 20v2"/><path d="M5 5h14v14H5z"/></svg>
        AI for Science
      </h2>
			<p>
				I am exploring how Large Language Models (LLMs) and autonomous agents 
        can transform scientific discovery, specifically through workflow 
        orchestration and automated data interpretation.
			</p>
		</section>

    <section>
      <h2>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="section-icon"><path d="M14.5 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7.5L14.5 2z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><line x1="10" y1="9" x2="8" y2="9"/></svg>
        Curriculum Vitae
      </h2>
      <p>
        For a more formal overview of my experience, you can view my 
        <a href="/cv" class="cv-link">Curriculum Vitae (PDF-style HTML)</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

		<section>
			<h2>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="section-icon"><path d="M19 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H9a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
        Personal
      </h2>
			<p>
				Outside of code, I enjoy cycling, HomeLab experimentation, indie games, 
        and basketball. I am an INFJ — committed to meaningful contributions 
        and open science.
			</p>
		</section>

    <blockquote>
      "MAGs lives matter" 🦀
    </blockquote>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-container {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.intro {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
	}

  .section-icon {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .cv-link {
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  blockquote {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
